<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF2014E600EF18997AC8E22" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF2014E600EF18997738882" blockId="16.[828,1437,393,1280]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E600EF18990CF8A82" bold="true" box="[828,958,393,416]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF2014E60F7F189971F8A82" author="JACOBY M." box="[965,1134,393,416]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Leyden Museum" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" pagination="201 - 230" part="6" refId="ref31117" refString="JACOBY M. 1884 b: Description of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera collected by Dr. B. Hagen at Serdang (East Sumatra). Notes from the Leyden Museum 6: 201 - 230." title="Description of new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera collected by Dr. B. Hagen at Serdang (East Sumatra)" type="journal article" year="1884" yearSuffix="b">JACOBY (1884b)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from four specimens: ‘There are now four specimens contained in the present collection which I take to represent two males, from Banka (v. d. Bossche), and two females, from Serdang (Hagen)’. He also mentioned some differences, particularly more the transverse pronotum in the two specimens from Serdang. I examined one 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF2014E663EF249962E8942" box="[1292,1375,585,608]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">syntype</typeStatus>
from Banka (RMNH, = Bangka Isl., 
<collectingRegion id="462391AAFFF2014E67B2F26997AB89A2" box="[1152,1242,617,640]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
) and a photograph of the other one (MCZ). Undoubtedly, both 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF2014E6634F28996128982" box="[1286,1379,649,672]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">syntypes</typeStatus>
from Banka are females. Thus the differences in the shape of the pronotum cannot be attributed to sexual dimorphism, but more probably they belong to different species. However, the two females from Serdang were not examined (probably they are deposited in the RMNH) thus I avoid to designate a 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF2014E60D3F34997358842" box="[993,1092,841,864]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">lectotype</typeStatus>
and the species identity needs further study. Tentatively I did not place this species into any species group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF2014E6068F3A997AC8E22" blockId="16.[828,1437,393,1280]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">
Some specimens labelled as 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF2014E67A4F3A997BF88E2" box="[1174,1230,937,960]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">types</typeStatus>
can be found also in the MSNG and BMNH but cannot be treated as 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF2014E665CF3C996ED88C2" box="[1390,1436,969,992]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
specimens. Two females from MSNG refer to specimens published by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF2014E60FDF40997068F02" author="JACOBY M." box="[975,1143,1033,1056]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" pagination="377 - 501" part="36" refId="ref31521" refString="JACOBY M. 1896 a: Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 36: 377 - 501." title="Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1896" yearSuffix="a">JACOBY (1896a)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF2014E67AFF409960D8F02" box="[1181,1404,1033,1056]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dorydea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF2014E67AFF409960D8F02" box="[1181,1404,1033,1056]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Dorydea nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is not quite clear if the male from the BMNH labelled as ‘type’ refer to the male specimen mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF2014E6662F44990FE8FA2" author="JACOBY M." firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" pagination="377 - 501" part="36" refId="ref31521" refString="JACOBY M. 1896 a: Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 36: 377 - 501." title="Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1896" yearSuffix="a">JACOBY (1896a)</bibRefCitation>
or to the series and drawing in 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF2014E67CBF46996E88FA2" author="JACOBY M." box="[1273,1433,1129,1152]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Zeitung (Stettin)" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" pagination="259 - 313" part="60" refId="ref31637" refString="JACOBY M. 1899: Descriptions of the new species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Dohrn in Sumatra. Entomologische Zeitung (Stettin) 60: 259 - 313 + 1 pl." title="Descriptions of the new species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Dohrn in Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1899">JACOBY (1899)</bibRefCitation>
. Another nontype male from Soekaranda (Dohrn leg.) mentionedin 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF2014E60FDF4A9971B8FE2" author="JACOBY M." box="[975,1130,1193,1216]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Entomologische Zeitung (Stettin)" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" pagination="259 - 313" part="60" refId="ref31637" refString="JACOBY M. 1899: Descriptions of the new species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Dohrn in Sumatra. Entomologische Zeitung (Stettin) 60: 259 - 313 + 1 pl." title="Descriptions of the new species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Dohrn in Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1899">JACOBY (1899)</bibRefCitation>
is also deposited in BMNH. However, I am not sure if these males are conspecific with the females from the 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF2014E672CF4E9973D8E22" box="[1054,1100,1257,1280]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
series or not.
</paragraph>
